file_name: File:Wovensouls Old Sumba Textile with Marapu.jpg
description: ['island in East Nusa Tenggara Province, Indonesia']
parsed caption:
Indonesian ceremonial cloth called Lau Witi kau or Lau Wuti Kau. Queens in
East Sumba gave these works of art as wedding as wedding gifts or trousseau to
their daughters, as a blessing of power of the Marapu. The Marapu is the first
deified ancestor of the clan and through his presence through such textiles
confers protection. The face of a marapu may never be depicted in the beaded
motif on the textile. Courtesy the Wovensouls collection, Singapore.

Mukherjee conferred three Kirti Chakras and Ten Shaurya Chakras to Armed
Forces Personnel for displaying conspicuous gallantry, indomitable courage and

Delhi on March 22, 2014. Five of the Shaurya Chakra were given posthumously.

Коммунистическая партия Российской федерации (КПРФ) призвала своих сторонников
и всех, кто не согласен с результатами выборов в Государственную думу,
прошедшими с 17 по 19 сентября 2021 года, присоединиться к всероссийской акции
протеста. В условиях фактического ограничения массовых мероприятий, из-за
угрозы распространения коронавируса, и при факте отказа в согласовании данного
мероприятия, оно было заявлено, как встреча с депутатами КПРФ.

description: ['one of the five main histone proteins', 'one of the five main histone proteins', 'one of the five main histone proteins', 'InterPro Family', 'eightfold protein complex found at the center of a nucleosome core particle', 'molecule that encodes the genetic instructions used in the development and functioning of all known living organisms and many viruses', 'complex comprised of DNA wound around a multisubunit core and associated proteins, which forms the primary packing unit of DNA into higher order structures']
parsed caption:
The histone octamer is formed from two subunits each of the four core
histones. The four H3 and H4 subunits form a tightly packed tetramer that
associates with two H2A/H2B dimers to form each octamer. About 147 bp of DNA
is wrapped around the octamer to form a nucleosome. Nucleosomes can be arrayed
in the loosely packed beads-on-a-string form of chromatin, but are generally
more tightly packaged into the 30-nm fiber. Fiber formation requires histone
tails and additional proteins, neither of which is shown here.[1]

AIA 1700 channel (as well as AIA 1600) often shows a web-like pattern of
bright areas that highlight places where bundles of magnetic fields lines are
concentrated. However, small areas with a lot of field lines will appear
black, usually near sunspots and active regions.

**Where:** Temperature minimum and photosphere

**Wavelength:** 1700 angstroms (0.00000017 m) = Far Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** Continuum

**Characteristic temperature:** 6,000 K (11,000 F)

parsed caption:
Beschrijving Frederiksplein - Paleis voor Volksvlijt  

Foto op blad 12 van een losbladig album betreffende de Internationale
Tentoonstelling van Voorwerpen voor de Huishouding en het Bedrijf van den
Handwerksman in het Paleis voor Volksvlijt: het tijdelijke fotografische
atelier en tentoonstellingszaal van de firma Wegner en Mottu op het
tentoonstellingsterrein. Ervoor poseert een groep mensen, onder wie mogelijk
Alexis Mottu en zijn firmanten (de heren met hoge hoeden op het bankje). Op de
achtergrond het schoolgebouw Frederiksplein 35-37.

A "Travertine" texture (limestone texture/natural stone texture) from
ambientCG. What exactly it is is stated in the file name. The asset can look
reflective or polished. It looks a bit like marble, but is a widely used
building material. "Color" indicates a color texture, "Ambient Occlusion" an
ambient occlusion, "Displacement" an elevation map, "Normal" a normal
distribution, "Metalness" the distribution of metallicity, "Roughness" the
roughness distribution and "preview sphere" a preview of the asset. The number
indicates the chronological order. A texture with a higher number was
published later than one with a lower number. The letter after the number
indicates a variant.

parsed caption:
le Planol is a village and commune of [Saint-Victor-et
Melvieu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint-Victor-et_Melvieu "w:Saint-
Victor-et Melvieu") in southern
[Aveyron](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aveyron "w:Aveyron"), in the Raspes de
Tarn region. It hosts a switching station on the 400 000V grid, transforming
down to 63 000V and 20 000V for local distribution.

description: ['historic commercial building in Wisconsin, United States']
parsed caption:
The former Chamber of Commerce in downtown Milwaukee, Wisconsin, also known as
the Produce or Grain Exchange, built in 1879, was for a time the world's
largest wheat exchange and is now a private commercial building. Designed by
E. Townsend Mix as a fireproof building in an eclectic style that combined an
Italian Renaissance interior with an exterior variously described as Modern
Italian or typical of Glasgow or Edinburgh, it has a basement level covered
with Minnesota granite, higher masonry of Ohio sandstone, and Cream City
brick. Its clock tower rises to a height of 175 feet.

AIA 1600 channel (as well as AIA 1700) often shows a web-like pattern of
bright areas that highlight places where bundles of magnetic fields lines are
concentrated. However, small areas with a lot of field lines will appear
black, usually near sunspots and active regions.

**Where:** Transition region and upper photosphere

**Wavelength:** 1600 angstroms (0.00000016 m) = Far Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** thrice ionized carbon (C IV) and Continuum

**Characteristic temperatures:** 6,000 K (11,000 F), and 100,000 K (180,000 F)

NASA, Alexander Gerst of ESA (European Space Agency), and Sergey Prokopyev of
Roscosmos near the town of Zhezkazgan, Kazakhstan on Thursday, Dec. 20, 2018.

where they served as members of the Expedition 56 and 57 crews onboard the
International Space Station.

file_name: File:029d Humpback whale tail at Ísafjarðardjúp (Iceland) Photo by Giles Laurent.jpg
description: ['species of mammal', 'rear appendage of organism', 'Nordic island country in the North Atlantic Ocean', 'fjord in Iceland']
parsed caption:
[Humpback whale](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Humpback_whale "en:Humpback
whale") tail (_Megaptera novaeangliae_) at Ísafjarðardjúp (Iceland). Each
whale has unique patterns on its tail, like a fingerprint. Based on a good
quality photograph of a whale tail, researchers can identify a specific
individual by comparing the photo with a database of photographed whale tails.
Using the GPS coordinates and the date of the photograph of each whale tail,
it is possible to study the migrations carried out by each individual. Some
humpback whales migrate tens of thousands of kilometres in a year. Image set
number 4 out of 6.

file_name: File:Soyuz TMA-09M crew shortly after landing.jpg
parsed caption:
NASA Flight Engineer Karen Nyberg, left, Expedition 37 Commander Fyodor
Yurchikhin of Roscosmos, center holding the Olympic torch, and European Space
Agency Flight Engineer Luca Parmitano sit in chairs outside the Soyuz capsule
just minutes after they landed in a remote area outside the town of
Zhezkazgan, Kazakhstan, on Monday, Nov. 11, 2013.  
The Olympic torch was launched with the crew of Expedition 38 to the
International Space Station on November 7. It was passed from one module to
the next and had its first spacewalk on November 9 with two Russian cosmonauts
as part of its international relay. Now back on earth it will continue its
journey to Sochi, Russia for the 2014 Winter Games. Yurchikhin, Nyberg and
Parmitano returned from five and a half months onboard the International Space
Station.

**Text Appearing Before Image:**  
_may be of value inguiding the mind to the central idea, and may oftenawaken
associations of the most far-reaching kind, butif the realisation of the
central idea itself is incomplete,no combination of accessories, however
ingenious, canproduce a genuine work of art. The equipment ofGiottos Fortitude
could hardly be made more sug-gestive than he has made it. A lion-skin is
tiedby the paws about her waist and shoulders, and thejaw rests as helmet upon
her head; her tower-likeshield presents a lion rampant to the foe whose
arrowsand javelins it has already shattered; heavily coatedwith steel and
leather, she stands on the watch, withweapon prepared to strike. Yet fortitude
is not theeffect conveyed: the face is of a brutal type, and theform so large
and coarse as to command horror ratherthan respect. This seems the figure of
one for whomdanger can have no meaning, rather than of one whoestimates it at
its true worth. Yet Giottos intentionbecomes clearer after consideration of
the vice he_  
**Text Appearing After Image:**  
_Photo, Ali7iari\ \\_Arena Chapel TEMPERANCE To face p. 155. THE ARENA CHAPEL
AT PADUA 155 opposes to Fortitude, which is not Fear or Cowardice,but
Inconstancy. He pictures her in the attempt tobalance herself upon a wheel
that rolls down a slopepaved with smooth marble; a part of her dress iscaught
up by the wind into the likeness of a secondwheel behind her head; she throws
one arm up, theother down, in a futile effort to gain the equilibrium;her
limbs are limp, and the expression of her facevacant. This is clearly the
image of one who is at themercy of every breath of circumstance, whereas
Fortitudestands rooted to earth with a rock-like resolution. Temperance and
Wrath. Giotto is not content to follow the custom of histime and suggest a
Temperance opposed only toGluttony, bearing a pitcher of water in her hand:
hisconception, as Ruskin points out, is far nearer to theGreek a-wtjipoavvn,
moderator of all the passions. Heuses a delicate and complex symbolism to
enforce thisidea. A bit_

description: ['altarpiece, screen or decoration behind the altar in a church']
parsed caption:
The altar of the St. Petrikirche in Soest (DE). It was built in Antwerp, ca.
1525, for the Klepping family. It shows St James, son of Zebedee and St Renaud
de Montauban, Andreas klepping and his sons (left outer wing), St Patroclus of
Troyes and St Andrew, Elseke Sudermann and her daughters (right outer wing),
Anna Seibdritt (upper left outer wing) and a female saint (upper right outer
wing).

file_name: File:Alfonso Ribeiro - 2017 Pebble Beach 3-M Celebrity Challenge.jpg
parsed caption: www.army.mil/article/182277/fairy_tale_for_soldiers_at_pe... PRESIDIO OF MONTEREY, Calif. -- Soldiers from Presidio's 229th Military Intelligence Battalion came out to represent the Army and witness the 3-M Celebrity Challenge charity event at Pebble Beach Golf Links, Feb. 8. The event was part of the AT&T Pebble Beach Pro-Am and held one day prior to the start of the PGA tournament. The celebrity challenge is played over five holes with twelve celebrities paired in teams and playing alternate-shot format for a total purse of $100,000 to celebrities' designated charities. Participating celebrities were Bill Murray, Huey Lewis, Larry the Cable Guy, Toby Keith, Kenny G, Clay Walker, Alfonso Ribeiro, Gary Mule Deer, Andy Garcia, Kelly Rohrbach, Kunal Nayyar, and Josh Duhamel. Official Presidio of Monterey Web site Official Presidio of Monterey Facebook PHOTO by Steven L. Shepard, Presidio of Monterey Public Affairs.

file_name: File:La alcaldesa en el homenaje a Rafael Altamira 07.jpg
parsed caption:
La alcaldesa de Madrid, Manuela Carmena, ha asistido esta tarde acompañada por
el tercer teniente de alcalde, Mauricio Valiente, y el concejal del distrito
de Salamanca, Pablo César Carmona, al acto que conmemora la nueva denominación
del Centro Cultural Fuente del Berro, que a partir de hoy incluirá el nombre
del jurista Rafael Altamira. Se cumple así el acuerdo del Pleno de la Junta
Municipal del Distrito del 19 de diciembre de 2017. En el acto han estado
también la concejal Rita Maestre, portavoz del Gobierno municipal, y la
concejal socialista Mar Espinar.

file_name: File:The Public Telecommunication System Designation (Diamond Cable (Newark) Limited) Order 1991 (UKSI 1991-1143).pdf
depicts: ['The Public Telecommunication System Designation (Diamond Cable (Newark) Limited) Order 1991']
parsed caption:
The Secretary of State granted to Diamond Cable (Newark) Limited on27th March
1991 a licence under section 7 of the TelecommunicationsAct 1984 to run the
telecommunication systems specified in Annex A tothat licence, in the whole of
the District of Newark and Sherwood. Acopy of the licence was laid before
Parliament on13th May 1991. This Order designates those telecommunication
systemsas public telecommunication systems. Consequently, by virtue of
section9(3) of that Act, Diamond Cable (Newark) Limited will be a
publictelecommunications operator when the Order comes into force on10th June
1991.

(which in Korean is a generic term for radish) and as _Joseonmu_ (Joseon
radish). It is similar to the Chinese radish (daikon), but the flesh is firmer
and more strongly flavored.

parsed caption:
**Model** \- Rosie **Year Taken** \- April 2014 **Camera** \- Sony A7R
**Lens** \- Carl Zeiss 85mm f/.4 **Location** \- Studio

_**Image Info**_

Im not sure if you noticed it from the previous images, but Rosie has a body
that looks, in the right light, like its been chiselled from a single piece of
marble. Seriously, she is a fitness model also and I had to take some shots
that showed this side of her off. It may, in all honesty, appeal to everyone -
but I think it works as an artistic image.

_**Rosie**_

Right, for those of you who actually read these little stories, and I know a
few of you do, this could take a while. Seriously, I warn you, there is so
much to say about this girl that I think Im going to be up a while.

Ok, so this is Rosie. And Im sure that when God made her, he did so out of a
single piece of fresh person material. You know you get those people who are
beautiful, but there is the odd thing or element that looks bolted on from the
leftovers of someone else? You know the type? Yeah, Rosie is not one of those.
She was made when God was having a good day, when he was fresh out of bed and
inspired. Seriously, she is flawless. And I do not mean this in a purely
aesthetic way, she is just a wonderful person to know. Yeah, I spent a few
hours with her today and I know this already...to tell you a secret, I knew it
after 10 minutes.

She is just so much fun to be around, so bubbly and so charming. She has a
natural beauty that makes you swear blind you saw her in the last Hollywood
blockbuster, playing the femme fatale you loved so much, yet her personality
reminds you of the unassuming girl next door who is always too shy to talk to
you. She is funny, cute, sexy, gregarious, charming, professional, and pretty
much every other compliment I could possibly pay her.

She is, by a country mile, the best model I have ever worked with and I base
this around not just her ability to model (which is top notch) but in her
ability to lose herself on camera. She is so relaxed and natural that Im sure
to her, modelling is a breeze. I could write these paragraphs of compliments
and praise for the remainder of however many characters Flickr will
allow...but you will see for yourself over the coming photos that she is, in
all honesty the most beautiful girl Ive ever met.

But what about the things which lay inside the mind of this amazing girl?
Well, she feeds off other peoples energy. Yep, we had a good long chat about
the energy which people give off that people like Rosie pick up. She is so
sensitive to these energies that they can often dictate how she feels in a
situation and I think this comes across in her smile. When she is happy, her
smile, in all honesty, ignites the room. I think she is a creature of emotion
and this, in my opinion, is the thing which sets her modelling apart!

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0211 channel (as well as AIA 335) highlights the active region of the
outer atmosphere of the Sun - the corona. Active regions, solar flares, and
coronal mass ejections will appear bright here. The dark areas - called
coronal holes - are places where very little radiation is emitted, yet are the
main source of solar wind particles.

**Where:** Active regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 211 angstroms (0.0000000211 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 13 times ionized iron (Fe XIV)

**Characteristic temperature:** 2 million K (3.6 million F)

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 1600 channel (as well as AIA 1700) often shows a web-like pattern of
bright areas that highlight places where bundles of magnetic fields lines are
concentrated. However, small areas with a lot of field lines will appear
black, usually near sunspots and active regions.

**Where:** Transition region and upper photosphere

**Wavelength:** 1600 angstroms (0.00000016 m) = Far Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** thrice ionized carbon (C IV) and Continuum

**Characteristic temperatures:** 6,000 K (11,000 F), and 100,000 K (180,000 F)

parsed caption:
Suchinta Chowdhury Chanchal (Bengali: সুচিন্ত চৌধুরী চঞ্চল), known as
[Chanchal Chowdhury](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chanchal_Chowdhury
"en:Chanchal Chowdhury") (Bengali: চঞ্চল চৌধুরী), is a Bangladeshi actor.
Critically acclaimed for his performances in Rupkothar Golpo (2006), Monpura
(2009), Television (2012), Aynabaji (2016), and Debi (2018), he has received
two Bangladesh National Film Awards for Best Actor and three Meril Prothom Alo
Awards for Best Actor.
